status_message:
Dear readers of IJ Review,

Every day I learn from your passion. I would like to continually find ways to respect you.

With this in mind, I have asked our team to stop the use of the word "frontrunner" in regards to 2016 coverage going forward.  Until American voters have had their say at the ballot box and caucuses, I want to strive to cover all the candidates with an open mind. 

I think it is a disservice to confer "frontrunner" status 17 months before an election, before candidates have even have had the chance to introduce their platforms to American voters. 

The Independent Journal Review has always been a "reader first" news company.  We want you to let us know who is resonating with you by the articles you share and the comments you leave.  We strive every day to be wise enough to learn from you. 

I have always believed the most important trait in journalism is listening, so as the campaign progresses, and the candidates come to your towns, your inboxes and your Facebook feeds, please let us know what impresses you or disappoints you. We will rely on you, IJ America, to help enrich our political coverage.  

Sincerely yours,
Michelle Jaconi
Executive Editor, IJ Review
